The famous Nigerian Journalist, Kemi Olunloyo has expressed her concern over the death of the 22-year-old girl, Bamise who was recently killed in Lagos State.
As you can recall, the BRT Bus Driver who carried Bamise was arrested and handed over to TVC News officials for interview.
Kemi Olunloyo recently reacted to the case. She used her official Facebook page to share her opinion. Below is a screenshot of her post.
According to Kemi Olunloyo, she said “The Commissioner of Police, CP Alabi must tell the public why he handed the BRT Bus Driver, Mr. Andrew Nice who is the suspect to TVC News for interview”.
“Who coached him on a new motive? Why is the DSS motive different? What kind of Public Relations disaster is this?” Kemi Olunloyo asked.
After she made this statement, many people started reacting and commenting on her post.
What is your opinion on this?


